data.enText: an area of red spots on a person's skin, caused by an illness or a reaction to sth

data.chText: 我醒来时长了一身皮疹。
data.enText: I woke up covered in a rash.

data.chText: 我一吃巧克力就长皮疹。
data.enText: I come out in a rash (= a rash appears on my skin) if I eat chocolate.
The sun brought her out in (= caused) an itchy rash.
a heat rash (= caused by heat)

data.chText: 大量；许多；（涌现的）令人不快的事物
data.enText: a lot of sth; a series of unpleasant things that happen over a short period of time

data.chText: 大量关于监狱生活的电影
data.enText: a rash of movies about life in prison

data.chText: 近一个月这一带发生了很多起入室行窃案。
data.enText: There has been a rash of burglaries in the area over the last month.
doing sth that may not be sensible without first thinking about the possible results; done in this way

data.chText: 你要是认为在这件事上谁都会同意你的看法，那就太欠考虑了。
data.enText: It would be rash to assume that everyone will agree with you on this.

data.chText: 不要草率行事，要三思而行。
data.enText: Think twice before doing anything rash.

data.chText: 这就是你贸然作决定的后果。
data.enText: This is what happens when you make rash decisions.

data.chText: 她轻率地答应借钱给他。
data.enText: She had rashly promised to lend him the money.

data.chText: 他对自己的莽撞极其后悔。

tr: a series of unexpected and unpleasant occurrences
any red eruption of the skin
marked by defiant disregard for danger or consequences
example: foolhardy enough to try to seize the gun from the hijacker
became the fiercest and most reckless of partisans"-Macaula
a rash attempt to climb Mount Everest
do something rash that he will forever repent"- George Meredit

value.def: If someone is rash or does rash things, they act without thinking carefully first, and therefore make mistakes or behave foolishly.

example.ex: It would be rash to rely on such evidence...
example.tran: 依靠这样的证据是草率的。

example.ex: Mr. Major is making no rash promises...
example.tran: 梅杰先生没有作出轻率的承诺。

example.ex: Don't do anything rash until the feelings subside.
example.tran: 在冷静下来之前不要鲁莽行事。

example.ex: I made quite a lot of money, but I rashly gave most of it away...
example.tran: 我赚了不少钱，但是大部分被我轻率地花掉了。

example.ex: My sister always said I acted rashly.
example.tran: 我姐姐总是说我行为鲁莽。

example.ex: With characteristic rashness and valor, Peter plunged into the icy water.
example.tran: 以他惯有的冲动和勇气，彼得一头扎进了冰冷的水中。

value.def: A rash is an area of red spots that appears on your skin when you are ill or have a bad reaction to something that you have eaten or touched.

example.ex: I noticed a rash on my leg...
example.tran: 我发现我腿上长了疹子。

example.ex: He may break out in a rash when he eats these nuts...
example.tran: 他吃了这些坚果可能会长皮疹。

example.ex: The symptoms include skin rashes, fever, and painful joints.
example.tran: 病症包括皮疹、发烧和关节疼痛。

value.def: If you talk about a rash of events or things, you mean a large number of unpleasant events or undesirable things, which have happened or appeared within a short period of time.

example.ex: They believe this confusion is responsible for a rash of suicides this spring.
example.tran: 他们认为今年春天一连串的自杀事件是由这次混乱引起的。

example.ex: ...one of the few major airlines left untouched by the industry's rash of takeovers...
example.tran: 没有受到行业内大量收购风波波及的少数几个重要航空公司之一

example.ex: Now a rash of scruffy little shops bordered one side of the street.
example.tran: 现在街道的一边排满了各种破旧的小店。

value.tran: 大量，许多（令人不快的事情）
